Author::::DerekNiemann
DateTime::::2016-03-10T09:08:17Z
Can't leave you on a cliffhanger, spiralx. Robins (and blackbirds too) are known for defending small territories so fiercely that it sometimes leads to a fight to the death. It's not (as anyone who has seen it will testify) a pleasant sight. A sharp beak can do damage but it takes a long time to kill a rival. Normally, one of the two backs down pretty quickly, so it doesn't get that far, but if the intruder really fancies his chances, they'll fight in earnest.



